narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Yes! It was a fascinating class discussing in depth the trade circles that linked the historical global, focusing on the Asian continent and its connections to Europe and Africa.

It's more like a lecture where Prof Siu talks and we listen, but the students don't talk much. nonetheless, Siu has interesting things to say. There is a lot of reading, but most undergrads don't do them. That said, the class is 60% grad students and 40% or less undergrad. Brings up fascinating topics but I'd like to see the class a bit more structured and less stream-of-consciousness style.

I would highly recommend this course to a fellow student. This is a great seminar taught by a great professor. It meets only once a week and you get to hear Professor Siu lecture on her area of expertise. Although there are a ton of assigned readings, you don't have to know every single detail, and Professor Siu guides you through the important topics and concepts.
Yes, I would. Fun topics, not too difficult and great professor
